<div><h3>ENG 180 - Major American Writers I </h3>  <hr>The sequence ENG 180-<a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=25&coid=81508" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=25&coid=81508&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=25&coid=81508&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt8918" target="_blank">ENG 181</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> takes an historical approach to American literature from Puritanism to the present. This course concentrates on early American literature, circa 1620-1860, by authors such as Bradstreet, Rowlandson, Edwards, Franklin, Emerson, Douglass, Dickinson, Whitman, Hawthorne, Melville, Stowe, and others. For undergraduate English majors and minors, this course satisfies the Historical Sequence (B-1) requirement. Meets the Verbal Expression (VE) requirement. This course also fulfills the Diversity and Inclusion requirement.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> VE, DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Every year<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt8918"></div></div>		</td>
